    <body>
        <section name="maven-scala-plugin">
            <p>The maven-scala-plugin is used for compiling scala code in maven. It hasn't been
            tested much and it has only been tested on Linux, so if there are problems please let me know.</p>
            <p>You'll notice the plugin only notices code in src/main/scala.  This means it can't be attached to the process-test-sources phase.</p>
        </section>
        <section name="Requirements">
            <ul>
                <li>Maven 2.0.4</li>
                <li>JDK 1.5</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section name="Goals">
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Goal</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><a href="compile.html">scala:compile</a></td>
                    <td>compiles scala source files in src/main/scala</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><a href="run.html">scala:run</a></td>
                    <td>runs a scala class</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </section>
